:: Page 11 {"position":"175,2125","size":"100,100"}
After I calmed down, I wiped the tears off my face, I look at Alice
  "It was three years ago, it was the final round of this district level competition. Bigger stage, bigger audience, bigger expectations. My coach whispered 'Good luck, Melisa. Don't mess this up.' At the stage, I sang with my full heart, but...." I stopped for a brief moment
  "Take your time" Alice whispered,
  "Okay, anyway, halfway towards the second verse, the lyrics vanished. For five. Five seconds that felt like years. I forced myself to continue, but it wasn't the same. It was written in their faces. Disapointment." I took a deep breath "I didn't win. Second place, was what I got. The ride home was quiet. Something inside me cracked that day. Because I failed at the one thing I was naturally good at" I frowned, a river was about to leak from my eyes.
  "That's it?" She looked at me with a smirk, but like, that smirk she makes everytime she comforts me.
  "That was everything, Alice."
  "You're not a machine, Lis. You're human. Don't give up your hobby just because of that." She said with her worrysome tone
  "Yes, Alice."
  "How about..... you sing something? I'll join in"
  "I... Sure" My frowny face turned upside down. For once, I was excited to sing
  
Alice picked //Dancing Queen//, a classic, we both pulled out our bottles to use as a microphone and sang with our hearts, fully
