:: Page 5 {"position":"300,800","size":"100,100"}
After that class just continued and nothing interesting happened. That was until the teacher asked a question about the subject. At least like, 11 people raised their hands. But I guess teacher had better plans. 

“Melisa, would you care to answer my question?” He lightheartedly asked. God, how do I tell him I’ve been zoning out during his class.
“I- uhh- um… I don’t know…” Well, that settles it. I’m done for.
“Okay, Will, what’s your answer?”

Jesus, What was I even thinking!? Now everyone is gonna see me as the stupid one! Today has been the worst!! I keep embarrassing myself over everything. What happened to me? Why am I like this? Why am I not like the old me? Back when I can answer everything, EVERYTHING so confidently or when I won every competition with ease. Now, Jesus Christ who even am I now? I haven’t done anything great or impressive. I even failed that test last week even after studying for 3 hours. Unbeknownst to me, I’ve been making expressions while having those thoughts, enough expressions for Alice to notice.

“Lis, you okay? What’s bothering you?” She suddenly asked me. Her sudden questio	jumped me from my thoughts. I frantically start writing on a piece of paper. I honestly don’t want to say it out loud.
“Read it” I said to her while handing her the note. The note read;
  //That moment, where I just stuttered and muttered nonsense after I was asked   			something really embarrassed me, Alice. Now I feel like a moron. I think everyone sees 		me as the stupid one now. Ugh. It’s just, I wish I can just be like me, you know?//
Alice looked up at me and wrote something back;
	//Meet me after class, at my locker//

[[Page 6]]



:: Page 6 {"position":"300,925","size":"100,100"}
I rushed towards the bathroom after class. That entire time I was hesitant to raise my hand and ask if I could go to the bathroom. After I was done, I immediately rushed towards Alice’s locker before next period starts. Thankfully, the school gives us students 15 minutes in between the first and second periods. As I kept speed walking, I made sure to not hit anyone on the way. Then, I see Alice, waiting. I go up to her

“Hey, I’m here. What did you wanna say?"
“Yeah, what do you mean by ‘I wish I can just be like me?’, I need to know what you’re trying to say there”
“Oh, well” I say as I scratched my nape, “I mean like, I wish I could be like the old me, smart and talented, y’know?” I answered her. What I got back from Alice was;
“People would kill to be like you, Lis. You’re not a moron, seriously. It’s okay to feel embarrassed, but it’s not okay to beat yourself up like that. And, no one cares if you don’t know the answer to a question. It’s not the end of the world. Besides, you’re already smart, you just need that confidence because the attitude you choose to have helps you a lot too.”

***

[[Page 7]]


:: Page 7 {"position":"300,1050","size":"100,100"}
Second period, history class, not the most likeable subject for me but better than chemistry, I guess. Thankfully, we were only given a sheet of paper to work with and that was just it. Mr. Cunningham even played a movie while we were working on it. Gave me a lot of time to just do nothing. Love Cunningham for that. Other than that, I’ve been thinking about what Alice said. 
	I don’t feel smart
Did Alice really tell the truth?? My hands felt heavy as my expression fades into worrisome. My legs quivered, thinking of ANY possibility in all this. Did she mean it? Or was she just lying to make me feel better?

The classroom lights suddenly felt too bright. The scratching of pencils on paper sounded sharper. Even the movie playing on the projector, some old historical drama felt louder than it should’ve been.

[[Page 8]]


:: Page 8 {"position":"300,1175","size":"100,100"}
You’re already smart.

If I’m smart… then why does everything feel harder now? Why do I reread paragraphs five times and still not understand them? Why did I study three hours for that math test and still fail? Why do I freeze every time a teacher calls my name? My pen hovered above the worksheet. Question three. I’d read it. I think. But the words blurred together like they were melting off the page. Maybe I peaked too early. I think I was only “smart” because the work was easy back then. I'm sure everyone else just caught up. Maybe they surpassed me. I swallowed.

What if they’re all secretly thinking it?

My grip tightened around my pen. What if the only… only reason teachers call on me is because they expect the “old me” to answer? And for all the time I say “I don’t know,” I’m just proving that she’s gone?

I felt a twist in my stomach. What if I’m disappointing everyone quietly? Mr. Cunningham laughed at something in the movie. A few students chuckled along. I didn’t even know what scene they were on. I blinked and forced myself to breathe.

[[Page 9]]


:: Page 9 {"position":"300,1300","size":"100,100"}
Okay. Wait. Alice wouldn’t lie. But maybe… she doesn’t see it clearly. She doesn’t feel what I feel.. Immediately comparing myself to everyone in the room. I don’t think she knows how everyone seems so sure of themselves. And I’m just-
What am I?
A former trophy kid? My stomach twisted, again. What if this is permanent? What if I never get that confidence back? What if this is just who I am now..? A hesitant, average, replaceable?

If I don’t join the singing competition, someone else will. If I don’t answer questions, someone else will. If I disappear from the spotlight..   My breathing grew uneven. I was about to lose control

[[Stop thinking. Take a deep breath]]
[[Think more. Maybe you'll get your answer]]


