:: Skip lunch {"position":"175,1750","size":"100,100"}
//Should I get lunch?//

That’s where Alice would go.
That’s where I usually go.

But the thought of sitting there, surrounded by noise and conversations and people… it made my chest feel tight again. And the thought of eating? Somehow worse. My stomach felt hollow, but not in a way that asked for food. More like a pit. I leaned against my locker and opened it, pretending to look for something. Maybe I’ll go in a minute. Just wait for the crowd to thin out. But a minute passed. Then another.

The hallway slowly quieted as most people disappeared toward the cafeteria. My locker door stayed open. I wasn’t looking at anything inside it. Just staring. I had been excited for lunch earlier. I even remember thinking about what they might be serving today. Now the idea of chewing anything felt tiring.

My fingers drummed lightly on the metal shelf. Maybe I’ll just skip today. It’s just one lunch. It’s not a big deal. I closed my locker quietly. The hallway was nearly empty now. Instead of turning toward the cafeteria, my feet moved the other direction. Toward the stairwell. It was one of the quietest places in the school during lunch. Each step echoed softly as I walked down the stairs and sat on the middle step. For the first time since all day… It was quiet.

***

After school, I decided to just go home when Alice suddenly came up to me from behind and asked;
	"Wanna go over to my place?"
    "uh-"


