I held my breath, then took a deep breath. Jesus. Okay, stop, maybe it’s best if I just… work on this. I looked back down to the question, number 3
	Huh? This should be… For once, I knew the answer
	That was… easy, Number 4 should be…
For the rest of the sheet, it for once wasn’t difficult. Okay, that’s nice. This feels nice. I guess Cunningham just wanted to give us an easy task. Pencils scratch in the background, along with a few people talking.

I finished the worksheet. My pores relaxed and my eyes soothed. I love it when the class just watches a movie, I'll always watch the movie. But, maybe not this time. I just want to sleep. Eyelids heavy, with a smile in my face, I fell into slumber. The rest was nice. Especially since Mr. Cunningham didn't mind us sleeping for today. 30 minutes in, I wake up to the sound of the bell ringing. Sweet, lunch time

